## Installation:

Step 1.) Clone down the repo and its submodules (used for vim plugins).

```
git clone https://github.com/walterscarborough/dotfiles.git

cd dotfiles 

git submodule update --init
```

Step 2.) Create local bash file to set dotfile home path

Create the .bash_local file and add the following to it:

```
#!/bin/bash
DOTFILES_HOME=$HOME/dev/dotfiles
```

Feel free to set the DOTFILES_HOME variable to wherever you've cloned this repo down into.

Step 3.) You will need to either copy or symlink these dotfiles to your home directory. I've written a tool for this: https://github.com/walterscarborough/dotkeepr. Alternatively, feel free to use any other tool that you prefer.
